==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*tīði-'': cognate with Old Saxon ''tīd'' (Dutch [[tijd]]), Old High German ''zīt'' (German [[Zeit]]), Old Norse ''tīð'' (Swedish ''tid'').

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ti:d/

===Noun===
'''tīd''' ''f'' (''acc'' '''tīde''' or '''tīd''')
# [[time]]: an interval of time, a specific period
# an [[hour]]
# a [[season]]
# a specific point in time
# a feast-day

[[Category:Old English nouns]]



